Suriya, whose full name is Saravanan Sivakumar, is a highly acclaimed Indian actor, producer, and philanthropist. He primarily works in Tamil cinema but has earned recognition across the Indian film industry for his versatile acting and commitment to different roles.

Early Life:
Born: July 23, 1975, in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India.

He is the son of veteran Tamil actor Sivakumar and has a brother, Karthi, who is also a well-known actor in Tamil cinema.

Suriya initially pursued a degree in business and has a background in engineering but chose to follow his passion for acting.

Film Career:
Suriya made his debut in 1997 with the film "Nerukku Ner", which was directed by Vasanth. However, his breakthrough role came in "Kaakha Kaakha" (2003), a police procedural drama directed by Gautham Vasudev Menon. His portrayal of a tough yet sensitive cop won critical acclaim, and he quickly became one of Tamil cinema's most sought-after actors.

Some of his notable films include:

"Singam" (2010): This action-packed film directed by Hari became a massive hit, establishing Suriya as a top action star. It also spawned sequels, which continued his success in the "Singam" franchise.

"Ghajini" (2005): A psychological thriller directed by A. R. Murugadoss, in which Suriya played a man suffering from short-term memory loss. His intense performance in this film was praised and it was later remade into a Hindi film, which starred Aamir Khan.

"Vaaranam Aayiram" (2008): A critically acclaimed drama where Suriya portrayed multiple roles, from a young man to his older self, showcasing his acting range and depth.

"24" (2016): A science fiction thriller directed by Vikram Kumar, where Suriya played a dual role as both a scientist and his villainous brother, displaying his versatility in handling complex characters.

Other Ventures:
Suriya has also worked as a producer through his production company 2D Entertainment, which has produced films like "Soorarai Pottru" (2020), a film inspired by the life of Air Deccan founder Captain G. R. Gopinath. The film received widespread critical acclaim, and Suriya's portrayal of a determined entrepreneur was appreciated by both critics and audiences.

Personal Life:
Suriya is married to actress Jyothika, who is also a leading actress in Tamil cinema. They have two children, a daughter and a son.

He is known for his down-to-earth personality and his active involvement in philanthropic work. Suriya has been associated with various charitable organizations and initiatives focused on education and healthcare.

In 2015, he was honored with the Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor for his role in "Soorarai Pottru."

Recognition:
Suriya has won several awards throughout his career, including Tamil Nadu State Film Awards, Filmfare Awards South, and others for his contributions to Indian cinema. He is recognized as one of the most talented and bankable actors in Tamil cinema, known for choosing diverse and challenging roles.

Legacy:
Over the years, Suriya has built a legacy not only as an actor but also as someone who contributes to social causes. His career trajectory showcases an actor who is willing to take risks and push boundaries, earning him a loyal fanbase both in Tamil Nadu and across the world.

